#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:106
msgid "Using Transifex"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:108
msgid ""
"Transifex_ is a platform that simplifies the manipulation of ``.po`` files "
"and offers many useful features to make the translation process as smooth as "
"possible. These features includes a great web based UI, `Translation "
"Memory`_, collaborative translation, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:114
msgid ""
"You need to create an account in their service and a new project before "
"start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:116
msgid ""
"After that, you need to install the `Transifex CLI`_ tool which will help "
"you in the process to upload source files, update them and also download "
"translated files. To do this, run this command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:124
msgid ""
"curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/transifex/cli/master/install.sh | "
"bash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:125
msgid ""
"After installing it, you need to configure your account. For this, you need "
"to create an API Token for your user to access this service through the "
"command line. This can be done under your `User's Settings`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:131
msgid ""
"With the token, you have two options: to export as ``TX_TOKEN`` environment "
"variable or to store it in ``~/.transifexrc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:133
msgid ""
"You can export the token to an environment variable, using an ``export`` "
"command, which activates it in your current command line session:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:139
msgid ""
"# ``1/xxxx`` is the API token you generated\n"
"export TX_TOKEN=1/xxxx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:140
msgid ""
"In order to store the token permanently, you can save it in a ``~/."
"transifexrc`` file. It should look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:143
msgid ""
"[https://www.transifex.com]\n"
"rest_hostname = https://rest.api.transifex.com\n"
"token         = 1/xxxx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:150
msgid ""
"Now, it is time to set the project's Transifex configuration and to map "
"every ``.pot`` file you have created in the previous step to a resource "
"under Transifex. To achieve this, you need to run this command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:162
msgid ""
"sphinx-intl create-txconfig\n"
"sphinx-intl update-txconfig-resources \\\n"
"    --pot-dir _build/gettext \\\n"
"    --locale-dir locale \\\n"
"    --transifex-organization-name $TRANSIFEX_ORGANIZATION \\\n"
"    --transifex-project-name $TRANSIFEX_PROJECT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:163
msgid ""
"This command will generate a file at ``.tx/config`` with all the information "
"needed by the ``tx`` tool to keep your translation synchronized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:170
msgid ""
"Finally, you need to upload these files to Transifex platform so translators "
"can start their work. To do this, you can run this command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:177
msgid "tx push --source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:178
msgid ""
"Now, you can go to your Transifex's project and check that there is one "
"resource per ``.rst`` file of your documentation. After the source files are "
"translated using Transifex, you can download all the translations for all "
"the languages by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:184
msgid "tx pull --all"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:185
msgid ""
"This command will leave the ``.po`` files needed for building the "
"documentation in the target language under ``locale/<lang>/LC_MESSAGES``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:189
msgid ""
"It's important to use always the same method to translate the documentation "
"and do not mix them. Otherwise, it's very easy to end up with inconsistent "
"translations or losing already translated text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:194
msgid "Build the documentation in target language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:197
msgid ""
"Finally, to build our documentation in Spanish(Argentina) we need to tell "
"Sphinx builder the target language with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:202
msgid "sphinx-build -b html -D language=es_AR . _build/html/es_AR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:205
msgid ""
"There is no need to create a new ``conf.py`` to redefine the ``language`` "
"for the Spanish version of this documentation, but you need to set "
"locale_dirs_ to ``[\"locale\"]`` for Sphinx to find the translated content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/manage-translations-sphinx.rst:210
msgid ""
"After running this command, the Spanish(Argentina) version of your "
"documentation will be under ``_build/html/es_AR``."
